body.description: Splish and splash — what baby doesn’t love a bath? The soothing warmth of the water and the sound of little hands slapping makes it a fun time for both parents and babies. Not only distracting your child while you get the ablutions done is important, but also adding a bit of fun and relaxation to bath time is necessary, this duck bath toys set can make a real difference. The water bathtub toys are bright enough to appeal to children and will be easier to spot in the water, also, the bright contrasting colors aid in visual development. They can float freely in the water, even if the baby tries to sink them. The yellow ducks make happy "BEBE~" sound. The easy-to-grasp net and ducks have small sized especially for the baby's hands, they are small enough for tiny hands to grasp and hold. Along with making bath time more enjoyable for your child, the toys will help them to learn. Squeeze and the fishing game can help your little one develop their hand-eye coordination and dexterity. When novelty starts to wear off, regular hunting contests with your toddler can continue to make bathtime interesting. Bathtime is something your little one really looks forward to, rather than an ordeal.
